erence becomes 3,000{\%} for the case of a 60° deviated well. For this highly-deviated well, readings corresponding to the conductive formation layer are about 30{\%} smaller in magnitude than those in a vertical well. Shoulder effects significantly vary in deviated wells. {\textcopyright} Springer Science+Business Media B.V. 2007.},
